Dr. Jill Biden gave opening remarks before a higher education panel at NBC's Education Nation Summit. She thanked NBC for dedicating time to the issue of education and emphasized the critical role it plays in the future of the country. As an educator herself, Dr. Biden highlighted the power of education to break down barriers and instill confidence. She discussed the Administration's commitment to supporting students and making college affordable and accessible. President Obama has set a goal for the United States to lead the world in the proportion of college graduates by the end of the decade. Dr. Biden emphasized the need to not only get students into college but also ensure they graduate. She praised the efforts of colleges and universities in supporting students throughout their educational journey. Dr. Biden also highlighted the importance of community colleges and announced the upcoming White House Summit on Community Colleges. The summit aims to bring together various stakeholders to discuss how community colleges can meet the job training and education needs of the country.